homas Moran, Louise Nevelson, John Frederick Peto, Maurice Prendergast, John Singer Sargent, and Andrew Wyeth, among others, showcase the unique artistic heritage of the United States and the creative culture of Maine. European traditions are represented by works from the hand of Max Beckmann, Marc Chagall, Gustave Courbet, Edgar Degas, Jean-Auguste-Dominique Ingres, Claude Monet, Henry Matisse, and Pierre-Auguste Renoir. The Museum is accredited by the American Association of Museums and adheres to best practices in developing and managing these works of art in the public trust."}, {"Identifier": "Description of Intended Use of Endowment Funds:", "ReturnReference": "Part V, Line 4:", "Explanation": "The Organization's intended use of endowment funds is for general operations, education, maintenance of collection and buildings, acquisition of art for the collection, wages, and other related expenses."}], "CollectUsedForPublicExhibition": "X", "CollectUsedForScholarResearch": "X", "CollectUsedForPreservation": "X", "CollectUsedForLoanOrExchPrgrms": "X", "SolicitedAssetsForSale": "1", "BoardDesignatedEOYBalance": "0.16000", "PermanentEndowmentEOYBalance": "0.81280", "TermEndowmentEOYBalance": "0.02720", "EndowmentsHeldByUnrelatedOrgs": "0", "EndowmentsHeldByRelatedOrgs": "0", "TotalOfBookValueLandBuildings": "13685943", "TotalBookValueOtherAssets": "2868720", "TotalRevenue": "3761700", "TotalExpenses": "5059635", "ExcessOrDeficitForYear": "-1297935", "NetUnrealizedGLOnInvestments": "5183097", "TotalAdjustments": "5183097", "ExcessOrDeficitPerFS": "3885162", "TotRevenueEtcAuditedFinclStmt": "8882358", "NetUnrealizedGainsInvestments": "5183097", "RevenueNotRptdF990": "5183097", "RevenueSubtotal": "3699261", "InvestmentExpensesNotIncluded": "62439", "RevenueNotRptdOnFinStmt": "62439", "TotalRevenuePerForm990": "3761700", "TotExpensesEtcAuditedFinclStmt": "4997196", "ExpensesNotRptdF990": "0", "ExpensesSubtotal": "4997196", "InvestmentExpensesNotIncluded2": "62439", "Expe